The employees who posted images of Zimbabwe&#8217;s new currency were sacked, with the bank that employs them was fined. JOHANNESBURG Central bank workers who posted pictures of Zimbabwe s new bond notes have lost their jobs.The state-run People s Own Savings Bank that employed them has been fined $500,000 for breaching a confidentiality agreement.Social media activists hailed the bank employees who leaked the first images of the new bond notes and coins as heroes.But the central bank has hit back.Not only has the Peoples Own Savings Bank been slapped with a heavy fine in a time of severe cash shortages, the workers have been identified and dismissed.The photos were leaked on Sunday night, hours before the notes were first released.Former Finance Minister Tendai Biti has criticised the central bank s clampdown, saying in a tweet that the bond notes are illegal anyway.